Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. Def appears in custody & w/Atty Alyssa Armbrust State Public Defenders Office.  Atty Mark D. Bensen for State.  Clerk: EZ.  Def given complaint, advised of charges, penalties and rights, and probable cause found.  Counsel advises defendant unsure what extradition is for.  Court orders commitment to the Washington County jail for not more than 30 days to await a Governor's warrant.  Court does not order bail as defendant remanded to the jail.
